rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type containing standard descriptors for the means by which an object came into the owner's possession, e.g. seizure, bequest, sale, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Acquisition Method

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property relating an acquisition method to all of the works of art that were acquired in this way. Note that the expected type of this property should eventually be changed to common.ownership_relationship, and the virtual property should be redefined.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Artworks Acquired in this Way

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A retail establishment that specializes in displaying and selling works of art.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Art Gallery

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all art movements. Art movements are the tendencies in art in which artworks are created with a common philosophy or goal that is followed by a group of artists during a period of time. Examples of art movements include Romanticism, Impressionism, and Expressionism.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Art Period/Movement

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an artistic movement to an artist who exemplifies this movement.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Associated Artists

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an artistic movement to a work of art that exemplifies this movement.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Associated Artworks

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an artistic movement to a date when the movement roughly began.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Approximate Beginning

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an artistic movement to a date when the movement roughly ended.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Approximate Ending

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all art series. An art series is a set of artworks with a common theme or aspect that ties the pieces together.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Art Series

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating a series of artworks to the artist who created the series.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Artist

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating a series of artworks to one of the elements of the series.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Artworks

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a series of artworks to a standard descriptor for the theme of the artworks.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Subject

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Visual artwork depicting this subject
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Artwork on the Subject

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all artworks. These are the pieces of art developed primarily for aesthetics.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Artwork

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating a work of art to the medium or form of expression of the work of art, e.g. photography, painting, sculpture, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Art Form

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating a work of art to categorization of the subject of the artwork, e.g. portrait, landscape, still life, history (grande genre), abstract art, scenes of everyday life (genre works, or petit genre).
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Art Genre

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property relating a work of art to a standard descriptor for the theme or motif of the work of art.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Art Subject

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating a work of art to the artist who created it.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Artist

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property relating a work of art to the series of artworks of which it is a part.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Art Series

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating a work of art to the date when the artist started to create it.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Date Begun

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating a work of art to the date when the artist finished it.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Date Completed

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating a work of art to the measurements (in meters) of the work.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Dimensions

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating a work of art to an edition of it, e.g. a cast of a sculpture or a print of a photograph.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Edition

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property relating an edition of a work of art, e.g. a cast of a sculpture or a print of a photograph, to the canonical version of the work of art.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Editions

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property relating a work of art to information about where the art was located throughout its history. Note that the expected type of this property should eventually be changed to common.location_relationship, and the virtual property should be redefined.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Locations

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating a work of art to a material from which the artwork is made, e.g. acrylic, oil, brass, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Media

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property relating a work of art to a standard descriptor of the period or movement that the artwork exemplifies.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Movement

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating a work of art to its support. The support is the base for a two-dimensional artwork. For example, the support of many oil paintings is canvas; for many lithographs, it is paper. This should not be used for the ground, which is the material applied to the support to prepare it, such as gesso.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Support

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Relationship collecting the data on an artwork's location. Properties include the artwork, the location, and the to and from dates.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Artwork/location relationship

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property specifying the artwork about which the location information is provided.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Artwork

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property specifying the date at which the given artwork could first be found at the given location.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: From

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property specifying the place where the given artwork was located.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Location

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property specifying the date at which the given artwork could last be found at the given location.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: To

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The manner in which the artwork was aquired (e.g. purchase, gift, bequest, etc.).
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Method of acquisition

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The date the artwork was acquired by this owner.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Date acquired

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The date the artwork was sold, donated, etc. by this owner.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Last date owned

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The person, people, institution, or institutions that own the artwork.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Owner

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: If the artwork was purchased, the currency in which the transaction occurred.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Purchase currency

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: If the artwork was purchased, the amount the owner(s) paid for it.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Purchase price

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all color. Colors are the visual perception properties that corresponding to categories such as 'blue', 'red', and 'green'.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Color

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a color to the hexidecimal number corresponding to the color.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Color Hex

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An individual or business that specializes in taking photographs for companies, e.g. to be included in marketing collateral.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Commercial Photography

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type representing the collection of all paintings. Paintings are the visual artworks that have been created by the application of paint to a surface.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Painting

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An individual or business that specializes in taking passport photographs.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Passport Photography

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An individual or business that specializes in taking photographs.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Photography

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An individual or business that specializes in taking portrait photographs.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Portrait Photography

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type representing the collection of all sculptures. Sculptures are three-dimensional artworks.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Sculpture

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all visual art forms. Art form is the specific shape, or quality an artistic expression takes. The media used often influence the form. For example, the formal qualities of painting are the canvas texture, color, and brush texture.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Visual Art Form

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property relating a type of artistic expression, e.g. photography, sculpture, performance, etc., to a work of art that exemplifies this type of expression.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Artworks

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type containing standard descriptors for the themes or motifs of artworks, e.g. religious art, still life, portrait, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Visual Art Genre

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property relating an art genre to a work of art that exemplifies the genre.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Artworks

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of mediums used in visual artworks. In this context, medium is the material used to create the work.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Visual Art Medium

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A support is a material on which a two-dimensional artwork is executed. Examples include canvas, paper, and wood. For example, the Mona Lisa is an oil painting executed on poplar board, so its medium is oil paint and its support is poplar.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Visual art support

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all visual artists. These are the artists whose creative works have a visual element to them. Important sub-classes of this type include painters, sculptors, and illustrators.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Visual Artist

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating an artist to a medium or form of expression the artist uses or used, e.g. photography, painting, sculpture, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Art Forms

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property relating an artist to a series of artworks created by the artist.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Art Series

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property relating an artist to an artwork created by the artist.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Artworks

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property relating an artist to an artistic movement of which he or she was a part.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Movement

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An individual or business that specializes in taking wedding photographs.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Wedding Photography
